{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/issues/20/comments/11381274.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/issues/20#comment-11381274"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/issues/20.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 20, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "title": "Attributes of child elements are not copied if no element description is available (gazebo issue 735)"}, "content": {"raw": "Yes,\n\nOriginally I tried to add code to copy the attributes, but if you simply change line 750 of  sdformat/src/parser.cc from\n\n```\n#!c++\n\nif (_sdf->HasElementDescription(elem_name))\n```\n\nto\n\n\n```\n#!c++\n\nif(true)\n```\n\n... you will get the problem.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Yes,</p>\n<p>Originally I tried to add code to copy the attributes, but if you simply change line 750 of  sdformat/src/parser.cc from</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_sdf</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">HasElementDescription</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">elem_name</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">true</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>... you will get the problem.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-07-22T23:59:57.961841+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Hugo Boyer", "uuid": "{3d87874e-7099-4981-b04f-57f0272faa7d}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d87874e-7099